		<IRequirement type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID 4d4553a7-aded-46d9-bc35-c2f9dd41c74a</_id>
			<_myState type="a">8192</_myState>
			<_name type="a">Authentication</_name>
			<_modifiedTimeWeak type="a">6.9.2026::10:23:30</_modifiedTimeWeak>
			<_modifiedTime type="a">6.9.2026::10:23:30</_modifiedTime>
			<_body type="a">{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1250\deff0\deflang1045{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset238{\*\fname Arial;}Arial CE;}}%0D
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 Authentication consists of entering 4 digits and comparing them with the password\par%0D
}%0D
</_body>
		</IRequirement>
		<IRequirement type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID 65b3da8f-d618-4b00-a1cc-283a13b1501e</_id>
			<_myState type="a">8192</_myState>
			<_name type="a">Colision_Detection</_name>
			<_modifiedTimeWeak type="a">6.9.2026::9:58:32</_modifiedTimeWeak>
			<_modifiedTime type="a">6.9.2026::9:58:32</_modifiedTime>
			<_body type="a">{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1250\deff0\deflang1045{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset238{\*\fname Arial;}Arial CE;}}%0D
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 Collision detection should take place in each period (iteration) of the gate movement and consists in counting by the infrared receiver the pulses sent by the infrared transmitter.\par%0D
\par%0D
1.If the number of pulses received and sent differ significantly, send an appropriate signal to the Controller, which should stop the drive\par%0D
\par%0D
2.Otherwise, keep moving.\par%0D
}%0D
</_body>
		</IRequirement>
		<IRequirement type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID 6d22d57e-7fac-45ba-9994-0f043b00b6c1</_id>
			<_myState type="a">8192</_myState>
			<_name type="a">Firmware</_name>
			<_modifiedTimeWeak type="a">6.9.2026::10:23:55</_modifiedTimeWeak>
			<_modifiedTime type="a">6.9.2026::10:23:55</_modifiedTime>
			<_body type="a">{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1250\deff0\deflang1045{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset238{\*\fname Arial;}Arial CE;}}%0D
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 Firmware Update\par%0D
}%0D
</_body>
		</IRequirement>
		<IRequirement type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID a2ad6ef1-ea45-42b6-b859-ae940206a70d</_id>
			<_myState type="a">8192</_myState>
			<_name type="a">Movement</_name>
			<_modifiedTimeWeak type="a">6.9.2026::10:26:26</_modifiedTimeWeak>
			<_modifiedTime type="a">6.9.2026::10:26:26</_modifiedTime>
			<_body type="a">{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1250\deff0\deflang1045{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset238{\*\fname Arial;}Arial CE;}}%0D
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 The transition to the gate movement in the given direction requires the following steps:\par%0D
\par%0D
1.Turn on the collision detector\par%0D
\par%0D
2.Optional activation of the signaling lamp\par%0D
\par%0D
3.Turning on the gate drive\par%0D
During the movement taking place in a given direction, the following actions should be repeated every fixed period of time:\par%0D
\par%0D
1.Send a signal about the last traveled distance to the Controller.\par%0D
\par%0D
2.Check the occurrence of a collision and if the collision detector signals it, stop the gate movement\par%0D
\par%0D
3.If the signaling option is active, flash the lamp.\par%0D
}%0D
</_body>
		</IRequirement>
		<IRequirement type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID c952be47-6be5-41e2-93a7-3f9886cdcdd3</_id>
			<_myState type="a">8192</_myState>
			<_name type="a">Recieving_Signal_From_RC</_name>
			<_modifiedTimeWeak type="a">6.9.2026::10:25:17</_modifiedTimeWeak>
			<_modifiedTime type="a">6.9.2026::10:25:17</_modifiedTime>
			<_lastID type="a">2</_lastID>
			<_body type="a">{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1250\deff0\deflang1045{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset238{\*\fname Arial;}Arial CE;}}%0D
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 After receiving the signal, the receiver should:\par%0D
\par%0D
1.Validate the recorded signal according to the defined requirements.\par%0D
\par%0D
2.If the signal meets the requirements, send it to the Controller for interpretation\par%0D
2.1. If the gate was moving at a given moment, it should be stopped, remembering the direction in which it was moving\par%0D
2.2. If the gate was at rest, start the movement in the opposite direction to the previous one\par%0D
\par%0D
3.If the signal is incorrect, ignore it.\par%0D
}%0D
</_body>
